than busier places like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/uvita\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Uvita<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/santa-teresa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Santa Teresa<\/a>. Expect to pay anywhere from 20 &#x2013; 250 USD a night for a room and 6 &#x2013; 30 USD for a meal. Most tours have a small entrance fee or donation. Note that tap water is safe to drink in Puerto Viejo town.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-budget\">\n        <span class=\"block-budget__title\">Budget<\/span><ul class=\"block-budget__list\"><li>\n                        <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                            <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                            <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                        <\/div>Hotel: 40 &#x2013; 200 USD \/ night\n                    <\/li><li>\n                        <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                            <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                            <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                        <\/div>Hostel: 10 &#x2013; 100 USD \/ night\n                    <\/li><li>\n                        <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                            <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--restaurants\"><\/span>\n                            <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                        <\/div>Price per meal: 6 &#x2013; 30 USD\n                    <\/li><li>\n                        <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                            <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--attractions\"><\/span>\n                            <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                        <\/div>Entrances: 2 &#x2013; 25 USD\n                    <\/li><li>\n                        <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                            <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--transport\"><\/span>\n                            <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                        <\/div>Transport: &#xB1; 20 USD \/ day\n                    <\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><div class=\"block-link block-link--tip block-link--long\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Helpful budget tip! <\/strong>The currency in Costa Rica is Colones. Save up a lot of exchange fees by converting your own local currency to Colones with a <a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/go\/transferwise\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Wise card<\/a>. You can use that card to withdraw Colones from the ATM in Costa Rica or pay by card at pretty much all the shops. Some restaurants charge USD by default, but it will significantly decrease the total bill if you ask them to charge Colones. <a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/go\/transferwise\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Get a Wise card here; it&#x2019;s free!<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-c